by javiereguiluz at 2019-07-04T18:09:55Z

After reading your comments, I've decided to redesign the feature. Now it looks like this:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/73419/60683311-6bf55000-9e97-11e9-8c39-a992b793ae3d.png)

I think it's a good balance between security and utility:

* We only display the "hidden results" message once, no matter how many results you can't see.
* We don't tell you how many results you can't see.
* The message is always displayed at the end of the listing, to not bother much.
* Thanks to this message, the user can (hopefully) understand why the number of results don't match exactly.

